stice/meta/color}}\" |\n| bgcolor=\"{{Civic Platform/meta/color}}\" |\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Undecided/would not vote\n|-\n! [[Andrzej Duda|Duda]]<br/><small>[[Independent (politician)|IN]]</small>\n! [[Rafa\u0142 Trzaskowski|Trzaskowski]]<br/><small>[[Civic Platform|PO]]</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background:lightsteelblue;\" | [https://wiadomosci.wp.pl/sondaz-zaskakujacy-zwyciezca-ii-tury-wyborow-prezydenckich-6366432101652609a IBSP]\n| 31 January-6 February 2019\n| 47.9%\n| style=\"background:#fbcc99;\"| '''49.3%'''\n| 2.8%\n|}\n\n====Duda v. Nowacka====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:85%;line-height:14px;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Poll source\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Date(s)<br />administered\n| bgcolor=\"{{Law and Justice/meta/color}}\" |\n| bgcolor=\"{{Your Movement/meta/color}}\" |\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Undecided/would not vote\n|-\n! [[Andrzej Duda|Duda]]<br/><small>[[Independent (politician)|IN]]</small>\n! [[Barbara Nowacka|Nowacka]]<br/><small>[[Your Movement|TR]]</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background:lightsteelblue;\"| [http://wiadomosci.gazeta.pl/wiadomosci/1,114871,20169831,2020-rok-ii-tura-wyborow-prezydenckich-kto-zagrozilby-dudzie.html#MT Millward Brown]\n| 20\u201322 May 2016\n| style=\"background:lightsteelblue;\"| '''50%'''\n| 30%\n| 20%\n|}\n\n====Kaczy\u0144ski v. Tusk====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:85%;line-height:14px;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Poll source\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Date(s)<br />administered\n| bgcolor=\"{{Law and Justice/meta/color}}\" |\n| bgcolor=\"{{Civic Platform/meta/color}}\" |\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Undecided/would not vote\n|-\n! [[Jaros\u0142aw Kaczy\u0144ski|Kaczy\u0144ski]]<br/><small>[[Law and Justice|PiS]]</small>\n! [[Donald Tusk|Tusk]]<br/><small>[[Civic Platform|PO]]</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background:lightsteelblue;\"| [https://www.se.pl/wiadomosci/polityka/najnowszy-sondaz-dla-super-expressu-tusk-przegrywa-z-duda-ale-miazdzy-kaczynskiego-aa-zo84-HVyF-BzTN.html Pollster]\n| 9\u201310 August 2018\n| 35%\n| style=\"background:#fbcc99;\"| '''65%'''\n| -\n|-\n| style=\"background:lightsteelblue;\"| [https://www.rp.pl/Polityka/308059943-Sondaz-PiS-jest-skazane-na-Andrzeja-Dude.html IBRiS]\n| 26\u201327 July 2018\n| 41%\n| style=\"background:#fbcc99;\"| '''50%'''\n| 9%\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist |group=nb}}\n{{notes}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Polish elections}}\n\n[[Category:2020 elections in Europe|Poland]]\n[[Category:Presidential elections in Poland]]\n[[Category:2020 in Poland]]\n[[Category:May 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2020 Polish presidential election\n| country = Poland\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = yes\n| previous_election = 2015 Polish presidential election\n| previous_year = 2015\n| election_date = 10 May 2020\n| title             = President\n| before_election   = [[Andrzej Duda]]\n| before_party      = Independent (politician)\n| posttitle         = Elected President\n| after_election    = TBC\n| after_party       = TBC\n}}\n\n'''Presidential elections''' are scheduled to be held in [[Poland]] on 10 May 2020. Incumbent president [[Andrzej Duda]] is eligible for reelection.\n\n{{TOC limit}}\n\n==Electoral system==\nThe President of Poland is directly elected using the [[two-round system]]. They are limited to two five-year terms. The term of [[Andrzej Duda]] will expire on 6 August 2020, and the president-elect will take oath of office on that day, before the [[National Assembly (Poland)|National Assembly]] (a joint session of the [[Sejm]] and [[Senate]]). In order to be registered to contest the election, a candidate has to be a Polish citizen, at least 35 years old on the day of the first round of the election, and have collected at least 100,000 voters' signatures by March 26, 2020 at midnight.\n\n==COVID-19 pandemic==\nOn 6 April 2020, during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Poland|COVID-19 pandemic]], the [[Sejm|Sejm of the Republic of Poland]] passed a bill which requires voting for the presidential election to be carried out by postal voting only. The bill was sent to the [[Senate of Poland|upper house]] of [[Parliament of Poland|Polish parliament]] for further processing. Among many law professionals, this solution raises a lot of controversy<ref name=\"Sejm_electionlaw_druk328_procedure\">{{cite web | language =pl | title= Poselski projekt ustawy o szczeg\u00f3lnych zasadach przeprowadzania wybor\u00f3w powszechynych na Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej zarz\u0105dzonych w 2020 r.  |trans-title = Parliamentarian law project concerning special rules for carrying out general elections for the President of the Polish Republic organised in 2020<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | website= [[Sejm]] |date =2020-04-06 | url = https://sejm.gov.pl/Sejm9.nsf/PrzebiegProc.xsp?id=E9F90DFB2E2E3CA0C12585420054AB28 | accessdate = 2020-04-07 |archiveurl= https://archive.today/iXDT1 |archivedate= 2020-04-07 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped --> |url-access = <!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free -->}} </ref>\n\n==Candidate selection==\nThe following candidates have been nominated by parties represented in the [[Sejm]].\n=== [[Law and Justice]] / [[United Right (Poland)|United Right]] ===\nIncumbent President Andrzej Duda is eligible to run for a second term. His approval ratings are high \u2013 in September 2017, his approval rating stood at 71% and in February 2018, at 72%, A record surpassed only by [[Aleksander Kwa\u015bniewski]] from 1995 to 2005, whose approval ratings surpassed 75%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dorzeczy.pl/kraj/40293/Sondaz-CBOS-Wielki-wzrost-poparcia-dla-prezydenta-Dudy.html|title=Sonda\u017c CBOS: Wielki wzrost poparcia dla prezydenta Dudy|website=dorzeczy.pl|accessdate=2 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polityka/cbos-prezydent-duda-z-najwiekszym-poparciem-premier-morawiecki-na-drugim-miejscu/lr073kx|title=Prezydent Duda z najwi\u0119kszym poparciem|website=fakt.pl|accessdate=2 March 2018}}</ref> On October 24, 2019 in an open letter to the elected members of the Sejm and Senate, PiS chairman [[Jaros\u0142aw Kaczy\u0144ski]] announced that the party will strongly support Andrzej Duda in next year's presidential election<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvp.info/45001985/kaczynski-zwyciestwo-w-wyborach-trzeba-przypieczetowac-reelekcja-andrzeja-dudy|title=Kaczy\u0144ski: Zwyci\u0119stwo w wyborach trzeba przypiecz\u0119towa\u0107 reelekcj\u0105 Andrzeja Dudy|trans-title=[[Jaros\u0142aw Kaczy\u0144ski|Kaczy\u0144ski]]: Victory in the elections must be sealed with the re-election of Andrzej Duda|work=wiadomosci.wp.pl|accessdate=29 October 2019|date=24 October 2019}}</ref>.\n\n'''Nominee:''' \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f1f1f1;\" colspan=\"30\"|\n<big>'''[[Independent politician|Independent]]'''</big><ref group=nb>The President of Poland traditionally resigns from party membership after taking office. Duda is officially an independent but his campaign is being endorsed and funded by [[Law and Justice]].</ref>\n|-\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em; font-size:135%; background:#073A76 ; width:200px;\"| [[Andrzej Duda|{{color|white|Andrzej Duda}}]]\n|-\n|[[File:Prezydent Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej Andrzej Duda.jpg|alt=|center|210x210px]]\n|-\n| [[President of Poland]]<br />{{small|(2015\u2013)}}<br>[[Member of European Parliament]]<br />{{small|(2014\u20132015)}}<br>Member of the [[Sejm]]<br />{{small|(2011\u20132014)}}\n|}\n\n=== [[Civic Platform]] / [[Civic Coalition (Poland)|Civic Coalition]] === \nDonald Tusk was widely expected to comeback in Polish politics to run for President, all the more so given that his European office expired at the end of 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parlamentarny.pl/badania-opinii-i-rankingi/wybory-prezydenckie-w-2020-r-czy-donald-tusk-ma-szanse-wygrac,3691.html|title=Wybory prezydenckie w 2020 r. Czy Donald Tusk ma szans\u0119 wygra\u0107?|trans-title=Will Donald Tusk have a chance to win the 2020 presidential elections?|work=Parlamentarny.pl|accessdate=28 March 2017|date=29 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wprost.pl/kraj/10052383/Schetyna-Marzy-mi-sie-zeby-Donald-Tusk-byl-kandydatem-na-prezydenta-koalicji-rzadzacej.html|title=Schetyna: Marzy mi si\u0119, \u017ceby Donald Tusk by\u0142 kandydatem na prezydenta koalicji rz\u0105dz\u0105cej|date=2017-04-26|work=wprost.pl|access-date=2017-10-07|trans-title=\"[[Grzegorz Schetyna|Schetyna]]: I dream of [[Donald Tusk]] being the ruling coalition's presidential candidate\"}}</ref> However, in November 2019, he announced he would not run for the Polish Presidency, citing that he has \u201ca bag of difficult, unpopular decisions since prime minister\u201d that would burden his candidacy. He is said to have been advised against a run by private opinion polls. He decided to run instead for the leadership of the [[European People's Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/donald-tusk-elected-president-of-european-peoples-party/|title=Donald Tusk elected president of European People\u2019s Party|last=Baume|first=Ma\u00efa de La|date=2019-11-20|website=POLITICO|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref> As a result, party leader [[Grzegorz Schetyna]] decided to hold a convention in order to nominate a candidate for president. The [[2019 Civic Platform presidential primary|primary]] was won by Ma\u0142gorzata Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvn24.pl/r/983976|title=Civic Platform's Ma\u0142gorzata Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska confirms her 2020 presidential bid|website=TVN24.pl|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://wiadomosci.gazeta.pl/wiadomosci/7,114884,25512314,znamy-kandydata-po-na-prezydenta-przeciwko-andrzejowi-dudzie.html|title=Znamy kandydata PO na prezydenta. Do pojedynku z Andrzejem Dud\u0105 stanie Ma\u0142gorzata Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska|website=gazetapl|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-14}}</ref>\n\n''' Nominee: '''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f1f1f1;\" colspan=\"30\"|\n<big>'''[[Civic Platform]]'''</big>\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em; font-size:135%; background:#FCA241 ; width:200px;\"| [[Ma\u0142gorzata Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska|{{color|black|Ma\u0142gorzata Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska}}]]\n|-\n|[[File:Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska 30 November 2019 03.jpg|center|200x200px]]\n|-\n| [[Deputy Marshal of the Sejm]]<br />{{small|(2015\u2013)}}<br>[[Marshal of the Sejm]]<br />{{small|(2015)}}<br>Member of the [[Sejm]]<br />{{small|(2005\u2013)}}\n|}\n\n\n''' Declared, but lost at the primary convention:'''\n\n* [[Jacek Ja\u015bkowiak]], Mayor of [[Pozna\u0144]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvn24.pl/r/986957|title=Mayor of Pozna\u0144 Jacek Ja\u015bkowiak to run in Civic Coalition presidential preliminaries|website=TVN24.pl|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref>\n\n'''Declined:'''\n* [[Donald Tusk]], [[President of the European Council]], former [[Prime Minister of Poland]] and a candidate in [[2005 Polish presidential election|2005]]. \n* [[Rafa\u0142 Trzaskowski]], Mayor of [[Warsaw]] since 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvn24.pl/r/985813|title=Mayor of Warsaw says he's not going to run for president|website=TVN24.pl|access-date=2019-12-02}}</ref>\n*[[Rados\u0142aw Sikorski]], Former [[Marshal of the Sejm]] and [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Poland)|Minister of Foreign Affairs]] and a candidate in [[2010 Civic Platform presidential primary|2010]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://polskieradio24.pl/art1222_2406318|title=Prawybory prezydenckie w PO. Rados\u0142aw Sikorski nie wystartuje|website=PolskieRadio24.pl|access-date=2019-11-28|trans-title=\"Presidential primaries in PO. Rados\u0142aw Sikorski is not going to run\" }}</ref>\n*[[Bartosz Ar\u0142ukowicz]], Former [[Ministry of Health (Poland)|Minister of Health]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fakty.interia.pl/polska/news-bartosz-arlukowicz-nie-wystartuje-w-prawyborach,nId,3343413|title=Bartosz Ar\u0142ukowicz nie wystartuje w prawyborach|website=fakty.interia.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-11-28|trans-title= \"Bartosz Ar\u0142ukowicz is not going to run in primaries\" }}</ref>[[Marshal of the Senate of the Republic of Poland|.]]\n*[[Tomasz Grodzki]], [[Marshal of the Senate of the Republic of Poland|Marshal of the Senate of Poland]]\n\n=== [[Polish Coalition]] ===\nIn December 2019, PSL chairman [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz]] announced that he will be launching a campaign for president.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.wp.pl/wladyslaw-kosiniak-kamysz-walczy-o-urzad-prezydenta-ruszyl-z-prekampania-6456559626012289a|title=W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz walczy o urz\u0105d prezydenta. Ruszy\u0142 z prekampani\u0105|last=Mie\u015bnik|first=Magda|date=2019-12-14|website=wiadomosci.wp.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f1f1f1;\" colspan=\"30\"|\n<big>'''[[Polish People's Party]]'''</big>\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em; font-size:135%; background:#1BB100 ; width:200px;\"| [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz|{{color|white|W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz}}]]\n|-\n| [[File:W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz Sejm 2016.JPG|center|200x200px]]\n|-\n| Member of the [[Sejm]]<br />{{small|(2015\u2013)}}<br>[[Ministry of Family, Labour and Social Policy (Poland)|Minister of Labour and Social Policy]]<br />{{small|(2011\u20132015)}}\n|}\n\n'''Declined'''\n* [[Pawe\u0142 Kukiz]], leader of [[Kukiz'15]], [[Sejm|MP]], candidate in [[2015 Polish presidential election|2015]]<ref>https://wiadomosci.wp.pl/pawel-kukiz-ma-kandydata-na-prezydenta-ale-stawia-warunek-6465074849503361a</ref>\n\n=== [[The Left (Poland)|The Left]] ===\nAt the beginning of January 2020, [[W\u0142odzimierz Czarzasty]] said in [[Polsat News]] that [[The Left (Poland)|The Left]] will nominate [[Robert Biedro\u0144]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.pl/polska/czarzasty-zglosze-biedronia-na-kandydata-w-wyborach-prezydenckich/k15czh0|title=Czarzasty: Zg\u0142osz\u0119 Biedronia na kandydata w wyborach prezydenckich|website=Newsweek.pl|language=pl|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f1f1f1;\" colspan=\"30\"|\n<big>'''[[Spring (political party)|Spring]]'''</big>\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em; font-size:135%; background:#ac145a ; width:200px;\"| [[Robert Biedro\u0144|{{color|white|Robert Biedro\u0144}}]]\n|-\n| [[File:JKRUK 20190219 ROBERT BIEDRO\u0143 KIELCE DSCN2269 (cropped).jpg|center|200x200px]]\n|-\n| [[Member of European Parliament]]<br />{{small|(2019\u2013)}}<br>Mayor of [[S\u0142upsk]]<br />{{small|(2014\u20132018)}}<br>Member of the [[Sejm]]<br />{{small|(2011\u20132014)}}\n|}\n\n'''Declined'''\n*[[Adrian Zandberg]], [[Sejm|MP]], co-leader of [[Lewica Razem]], co-chairman of [[The Left (Poland)|The Left]]. <ref>https://www.wprost.pl/wybory-prezydenckie-2020/10289910/zandberg-wyjasnil-dlaczego-nie-startuje-w-wyborach-prezydenckich-umowilismy-sie.html</ref>\n\n=== [[Confederation Liberty and Independence]] === \nThe party held an [[open primary]], a first in Polish politics. The [[2019\u201320 Confederation presidential primary]] is modeled on the US style, with various rounds. [[Krzysztof Bosak]] was nominated during the final round of voting held at the convention in Warsaw on January 18. \n\n'''Nominee:'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f1f1f1;\" colspan=\"30\"|\n<big>'''[[Confederation Liberty and Independence|Confederation]]<br>[[National Movement (Poland)|National Movement]]'''</big>\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em; font-size:135%; background:#122746  ; width:200px;\"| [[Krzysztof Bosak|{{color|white|Krzysztof Bosak}}]]\n|-\n| [[File:Krzysztof Bosak Sejm 2016.jpg|center|200x200px]]\n|-\n| Member of the [[Sejm]]<br />{{small|(2005\u20132007, 2019\u2013)}}\n|}\n\n''' Declared, but lost in the primary election: '''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rp.pl/Konfederacja/191119512-Braun-Bosak-Korwin-Mikke-Konfederacja-oglosila-kandydatow-na-prezydenta.html|title=Braun, Bosak, Korwin-Mikke. Konfederacja og\u0142osi\u0142a kandydat\u00f3w na kandydat\u00f3w na prezydenta.|trans-title=Braun, Bosak, Korwin-Mikke. Confederation announced presidential primary candidates.|work=rp.pl|accessdate=30 October 2019}}</ref>:\n\n* [[Konrad Berkowicz]], [[Sejm|MP]], vice-chairman of [[KORWiN (Poland)|KORWiN]]\n* [[Grzegorz Braun]], [[Sejm|MP]], chairman of [[Confederation of the Polish Crown|KKP]]\n* [[Artur Dziambor]], [[Sejm|MP]], vice-chairman of [[KORWiN (Poland)|KORWiN]]\n* [[Janusz Korwin-Mikke]], [[Sejm|MP]], chairman of [[KORWiN (Poland)|KORWiN]]\n* [[Pawe\u0142 Skutecki]], former [[Sejm|MP]] from [[Kukiz'15]]\n* [[Krzysztof To\u0142wi\u0144ski]], former [[Sejm|MP]] from [[Law and Justice]]\n* [[Jacek Wilk]], former [[Sejm|MP]] from [[KORWiN (Poland)|KORWiN]]\n* Magdalena Zi\u0119tek-Wielomska, wife of [[Adam Wielomski]]\n\n=== Other candidates ===\nThese are candidates who collected 100,000 signatures supporting their candidacy but are not supported by parties currently in the Sejm. \n<gallery>\nFile:Ho\u0142ownia Szymon.jpg|Journalist '''[[Szymon Ho\u0142ownia]]''' (Independent) \nFile:Marek Jakubiak Sejm 2016.JPG|Former MP '''Marek Jakubiak''' (Independent)\nFile:Miros\u0142aw Piotrowski (Martin Rulsch) 1.jpg|Former MEP '''[[Miros\u0142aw Piotrowski]]''' (Real Europe Movement)\nFile:Pawe\u0142 Tanajno (cropped).jpg|Entrepreneur '''[[Pawe\u0142 Tanajno]]''' (Independent)\nFile:Stanis\u0142aw \u017b\u00f3\u0142tek.JPG|Former MEP '''[[Stanis\u0142aw \u017b\u00f3\u0142tek]]''' ([[Congress of the New Right]]) (PolEXIT)\n</gallery>\n\n===Rejected candidates===\nThese are candidates who failed to submit 100,000 signatures supporting their run by the March 26th deadline.\n{{colbegin}}\n* '''Zbigniew Adamczyk''' \u2013 Chairman of the Slavic Union \n* '''Piotr Bakun''' \u2013 Economist\n* '''Adam Bednarczyk''' \u2013 Activist in the Polish Nation Organization \u2013 Polish League\n* '''Marcin Bugajski''' \u2013 Political scientist \n* '''Roland Dubowski''' \u2013 President of the Association of Heirs of Polish War Veterans of the Second World War\n* '''Jolanta Duda''' \u2013 Businesswoman \n* '''Artur G\u0142owacki''' \u2013 Businessman \n* '''S\u0142awomir Grzywa''' \u2013 Leader of \"Sami Swoi\" (\"All Good Friends\")\n* '''Maria Le\u015bniak-Wojciechowska''' \u2013 Political activist\n* '''Wies\u0142aw Lewicki''' \u2013 Chairman of \"Normalny Kraj\" (\"Normal Country\")\n* '''Dariusz \u0141aska''' \u2013 Political activist\n* '''\u0141ukasz Malczyk''' \u2013 Chairman of the Union of Polish Entrepreneurs\n* '''Wojciech Mate\u0144ka''' \u2013 Candidate of \"Patriotic Poland\" \n* '''Andrzej Olszewski''' \u2013 Political activist\n* '''Marek Olszewski''' \u2013 Candidate of the [[Movement for Reconstruction of Poland|ROP]] \n* '''Bogdan Paw\u0142owski''' \u2013 Businessman \n* '''Andrzej Dariusz Placzy\u0144ski''' \u2013 Businessman \n* '''Wojciech Podjacki''' \u2013 Chairman of the \"League of Defense of Sovereignty\" \n* '''Jan Zbigniew Potocki''' \u2013 Self-declared President \n* '''Kajetan Pyrzy\u0144ski''' \u2013 Pensioner rights activist \n* '''[[Leszek Samborski]]''' \u2013 Former Member of the Sejm\n* '''Grzegorz Sowa''' \u2013 Businessman associated with 1Polska.pl\n* '''Romuald Starosielec''' \u2013 Journalist supported by \"Unity of the Nation\"\n* '''Pawe\u0142 \u015awito\u0144''' \u2013 Businessman \n* '''Krzysztof Urbanowicz''' \u2013 Political activist \n* '''Andrzej Voigt''' \u2013 Businessman \n* '''Jerzy Walkowiak''' \u2013 Political activist \n* '''Zbigniew Weso\u0142owski''' \u2013 Leader of the \"World Movement of Poles and Polonia\"\n* '''[[Waldemar Witkowski]]''' \u2013 Former Deputy Voivode and Chairman 