{"title_page": "Sabana Llana Sur, San Juan, Puerto Rico", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Sabana Llana, Juana D\u00edaz, Puerto Rico}}\n{{short description|Barrio of Puerto Rico}}\n\n'''Sabana Llana Sur''' is one of the 18 [[barrio]]s in the municipality of [[San Juan, Puerto Rico]].<ref name=Census>[https://www.census.gov/prod/cen2000/phc-3-53-eng.pdf Puerto Rico 2000: Population and Housing Unit Counts]</ref>\n\n==Population==\n{{As of|2000}}, Sabana Llana Sur had a total population of about 44,000 inhabitants.<ref name=Census/>\n\n==Location==\nSabana Llana Sur is located east of [[Oriente, San Juan, Puerto Rico|Oriente]], north of [[Trujillo Alto]] and west of [[Carolina, Puerto Rico|Carolina]]. It is bordered by the [[San Jos\u00e9 Lagoon]] on top, its closest body of water.\n\n==Territories==\nSabana Llana Sur has the following features.\n*   Population: ~44,000<ref name=Census/> - Land: Area: {{convert|4.17|sqmi|sqkm}} - Total Area: {{convert|4.17|sqmi|sqkm}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of communities in Puerto Rico]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{San Juan, Puerto Rico}}\n\n[[Category:R\u00edo Piedras, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Barrios of San Juan, Puerto Rico]]\n\n\n{{PuertoRico-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Barrio of Puerto Rico}}\n{{Distinguish|Sabana Llana, Juana D\u00edaz, Puerto Rico}}\n\n'''Sabana Llana Sur''' is one of the 18 [[barrio]]s in the municipality of [[San Juan, Puerto Rico]].<ref name=Census>[https://www.census.gov/prod/cen2000/phc-3-53-eng.pdf Puerto Rico 2000: Population and Housing Unit Counts]</ref>\n\n==Population==\n{{As of|2000}}, Sabana Llana Sur had a total population of about 44,000 inhabitants.<ref name=Census/>\n\n==Location==\nSabana Llana Sur is located east of [[Oriente, San Juan, Puerto Rico|Oriente]], north of [[Trujillo Alto]] and west of [[Carolina, Puerto Rico|Carolina]]. It is bordered by the [[San Jos\u00e9 Lagoon]] on top, its closest body of water.\n\n==Territories==\nSabana Llana Sur has the following features.\n*   Population: ~44,000<ref name=Census/> - Land: Area: {{convert|4.17|sqmi|sqkm}} - Total Area: {{convert|4.17|sqmi|sqkm}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{San Juan, Puerto Rico}}\n\n[[Category:R\u00edo Piedras, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Barrios of San Juan, Puerto Rico]]\n\n\n{{PuertoRico-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "The Eloquent Peasant", "label": "safe", "comment": "add List of communities in Puerto Rico to See also section", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabana_Llana_Sur,_San_Juan,_Puerto_Rico"}
{"title_page": "Hal Clements", "text_new": "'''Hal Clements''' was an actor and director of and in dozens [[silent film]]s. He married writer [[Olga Printzlau]].\n\nClements was part of Kalem's Jacksonville film crew.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UtFlWOHc7nYC&pg=PA241&dq=%22hal+clements%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj4qPC4s_DoAhVRiOAKHcsgBN4Q6AEIYzAI#v=onepage&q=%22hal+clements%22&f=false|title=The Sounds of Early Cinema|first1=Richard|last1=Abel|first2=Rick R.|last2=Altman|date=October 3, 2001|publisher=Indiana University Press|via=Google Books}}</ref> In 1914, he directed and managed the studio's comedy unit in [[Santa Monica]] featuring [[Ruth Roland]] and [[John Brennan (actor)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UEs_AAAAYAAJ&pg=PA671&dq=%22hal+clements%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnxaWRtfDoAhWmVN8KHShWADo4ChDoATADegQIARAW#v=onepage&q=%22hal+clements%22&f=false|title=The Moving Picture World|date=April 17, 1914|publisher=Chalmers Publishing Company|via=Google Books}}</ref> He portrayed General John Pershing in a [[Thomas Ince]] film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ihpdK6a2AfAC&pg=PA143&dq=%22hal+clements%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj4qPC4s_DoAhVRiOAKHcsgBN4Q6AEIWzAH#v=onepage&q=%22hal+clements%22&f=false|title=Thomas Ince: Hollywood's Independent Pioneer|first=Brian|last=Taves|date=April 17, 2012|publisher=University Press of Kentucky|via=Google Books}}</ref> In 1916 he was managing director of the new Gate City Feature Film Company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1qgbAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA958&lpg=PA958&dq=%22hal+clements%22+obituary+film&source=bl&ots=0Kr1ZJPW-j&sig=ACfU3U0qjiTcOfjJb_0zk5Cg7kzYz9CtZg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjwqeqwuPDoAhXyQ98KHZFBBoYQ6AEwAXoECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=%22hal+clements%22+obituary+film&f=false|title=The Moving Picture World|date=April 17, 1916|publisher=World Photographic Publishing Company|via=Google Books}}</ref>''\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[Uncle Tom's Cabin (1913 film)]