{"title_page": "1832 in Belgium", "text_new": "{{Year in Belgium|1832}}\nEvents in the year '''1832 in [[Belgium]]'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n:[[Monarch]]: [[Leopold I of Belgium|Leopold I]]\n:[[Prime Minister of Belgium|Head of government]]: [[F\u00e9lix de Muelenaere]] (to 20 October); [[Albert Joseph Goblet d'Alviella]] (from 20 October)\n\n==Events==\n[[File:Belegering der Citadel van Antwerpen, December 1832..jpg|thumb|Siege of Antwerp, 1832]]\n* 8 April \u2013 [[Engelbert Sterckx]] consecrated as [[Archbishop of Mechelen]]\n* 11 July\n**[[Order of Leopold (Belgium)|Order of Leopold]] established.<ref name=Overall>William Henry Overall, ''The dictionary of chronology, or historical and statistical register'' (London, 1870), p. 76.</ref>\n**Provisional postal convention between Belgium and the [[Thurn-und-Taxis Post|Office of the Prince of Tour and Taxis]] signed in [[Frankfurt am Main]].<ref>''Convention postale provisoire entre la Belgique et l'Office du Prince de la Tour et Taxis, sign\u00e9e \u00e0 Francfort-sur-le-Main le 11 juillet 1832'' [http://reflex.raadvst-consetat.be via refLex]</ref>\n* 9 August \u2013 [[Leopold I of Belgium]] marries [[Louise of Orl\u00e9ans]].<ref name=Overall/>\n* 20 October \u2013 [[Albert Joseph Goblet d'Alviella]] replaces [[F\u00e9lix de Muelenaere]] as Prime Minister\n* 15 November to 23 December \u2013 [[Siege of Antwerp (1832)|Siege of Antwerp]]: Belgian army with French support invests [[Antwerp Citadel]], held by Dutch forces.\n* 23 December \u2013 [[Siege of Antwerp (1832)|Siege of Antwerp]] concludes: Dutch forces removed from [[Antwerp Citadel]].\n\n==Publications==\n* ''Almanach de poche de Bruxelles'' (Brussels, M.-E. Rampelbergh)<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Hcs_AAAAcAAJ On Google Books]</ref>\n* ''Annuaire industriel et administratif de la Belgique par province: Province du Brabant'' (Brussels)<ref>[https://books.google.be/books?id=3kVbAAAAQAAJ On Google Books]</ref>\n\n==Art and architecture==\n;Paintings\n